1) Find all employees in the database who earn more than each employee of  Small  Bank  Coorporation 
2) Assume that the company is may be located in several cities. Find all companies located in every city 
in which Small Bank Coorporation is located. 
3) Find all employees who earn more than the average salary of all employees of their companies. 
4) Find the company that has the most employees. 
5) Find the company that has the smallest payroll. 
6) Find those companies whose employees earn a higher salary, on average, than the average salary at 
First Bank Coorporation.  
7) Modify the database so that “Jones” now lives in Newtown.




CREATE TABLE Employee(
    employee_name VARCHAR2(50),
    street VARCHAR2(50),
    city VARCHAR2(50)
);

CREATE TABLE Works(
    employee_name VARCHAR2(50),
    company_name VARCHAR2(50),
    salary NUMBER
);

CREATE TABLE Company(
    company_name VARCHAR2(50),
    city VARCHAR2(50)
);

CREATE TABLE Manages(
    employee_name VARCHAR2(50),
    manager_name VARCHAR2(50)
);

